SIMPLE: glean
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glean
<hw>Glean</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Gleaned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gleaning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>glenen</ets>, OF.
<ets>glener</ets>, <ets>glaner</ets>, F. <ets>glaner</ets>, fr. LL.
<ets>glenare</ets>; cf. W. <ets>glan</ets> clean, <ets>glanh<?/u</ets>
to clean, purify, or AS. <ets>gelm</ets>, <ets>gilm</ets>, a
hand<?/ul.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To gather after a reaper; to collect in scattered or
fragmentary parcels, as the grain left by a reaper, or grapes left after
the gathering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>glean</qex> the broken ears after the man⟦br⟧
That the main harvest reaps.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To gather from (a field or vineyard) what is
left.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To collect with patient and minute labor; to pick
out; to obtain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Content to <qex>glean</qex> what we can from . . .
experiments.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glean</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glean
<hw>Glean</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gather stalks or
ears of grain left by reapers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And she went, and came, and <qex>gleaned</qex> in the field after
the reapers.</q> <rj><qau>Ruth ii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pick up or gather anything by degrees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Piecemeal they this acre first, then that;⟦br⟧
<qex>Glean</qex> on, and gather up the whole estate.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glean</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Glean
<hw>Glean</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A collection made by
gleaning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>gleans</qex> of yellow thyme distend his thighs.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glean</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Glean
<hw>Glean</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Cleaning; afterbirth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gleaner</ent>⟦br⟧
